WEBVTT

00:03.887 --> 00:07.084
Oh, these are beautiful.

00:07.124 --> 00:08.716
Tell everyone I said thank you.

00:08.759 --> 00:09.953
I will.

00:09.993 --> 00:11.620
Oh, Donna said she'd be by

00:11.661 --> 00:14.892
tomorrow to bring you
her own present.

00:14.931 --> 00:16.990
Look, Kel...

00:17.033 --> 00:18.557
um...

00:18.602 --> 00:20.536
I'm really sorry.

00:20.570 --> 00:23.733
I-I should have been there
for you, and I-I wasn't.

00:23.774 --> 00:25.002
No.

00:25.041 --> 00:28.533
I'm the one who
shut everybody out.

00:28.578 --> 00:30.375
If I had called you,

00:30.413 --> 00:31.539
you would have been there.

00:31.581 --> 00:32.707
I know that.

00:32.749 --> 00:35.582
Well, if you need anything,

00:35.619 --> 00:37.587
please don't be afraid
to ask, okay?

00:37.621 --> 00:39.612
Thanks,

00:39.656 --> 00:42.056
but I know that in the end,

00:42.092 --> 00:44.526
I'm the only one
who's going to change anything.

00:44.561 --> 00:46.051
I didn't think

00:46.096 --> 00:48.064
I was gonna get through this,

00:48.098 --> 00:51.090
but maybe I will.

00:53.236 --> 00:54.703
Hi.

00:57.207 --> 00:58.572
Can I come in?

01:01.344 --> 01:02.606
Gonna be okay?

01:02.646 --> 01:04.409
Yeah.

01:04.447 --> 01:06.438
Colin and I need to talk.

01:06.483 --> 01:09.577
Dr. Weldon, please report
to the dayroom.

01:09.619 --> 01:11.678
Dr. Weldon,
please report to the dayroom.

01:11.721 --> 01:14.349
I'll call you as soon
as I get back from Mammoth.

01:14.391 --> 01:15.949
Okay. All right,
have fun snowboarding.

01:15.992 --> 01:17.584
- All right.
- Bye.

01:23.300 --> 01:25.291
These are for you.

01:27.037 --> 01:29.028
Thank you.

01:32.375 --> 01:34.400
How you been?

01:34.444 --> 01:36.742
Better.

01:36.780 --> 01:38.748
Yeah, me, too.

01:38.782 --> 01:40.750
One week,

01:40.817 --> 01:42.682
absolutely clean.

01:42.719 --> 01:45.552
That's great.

01:45.589 --> 01:46.988
You could do the same thing,
you know.

01:47.023 --> 01:49.014
You don't need to be here.

01:49.059 --> 01:50.924
You don't need a rehab unit.

01:52.863 --> 01:54.262
We could do this together.

01:54.297 --> 01:55.730
Colin.

02:01.071 --> 02:03.699
I know things got out of hand.

02:03.773 --> 02:06.207
And I know things had to stop.

02:06.243 --> 02:07.403
But it doesn't mean

02:07.444 --> 02:09.502
that you and I can't
get through this.

02:09.545 --> 02:11.810
Don't you see?

02:11.848 --> 02:13.782
We're not good for each other.

02:15.619 --> 02:17.610
That sounds so rehearsed.

02:18.955 --> 02:21.947
Is that what they told you
to say to me?

02:21.992 --> 02:23.721
No.

02:23.760 --> 02:26.024
This is me. This is how I feel.

02:26.062 --> 02:27.859
I can't see you anymore.

02:30.300 --> 02:33.326
I want you to know
that I'm not blaming you.

02:33.370 --> 02:34.837
You know,

02:34.871 --> 02:36.839
it was a two-way street.

02:39.109 --> 02:41.441
That's it, huh?

02:41.478 --> 02:44.345
I guess I don't have any say
in this, do I?

02:46.716 --> 02:48.479
Some two-way street.

02:51.054 --> 02:53.488
You know I love you.

02:53.523 --> 02:55.252
It's over.

02:55.292 --> 02:56.520
I'm sorry.

